-------------
Other Changes
-------------

Automatic Username Determination
--------------------------------

In addition to supporting the GSI GSSAPI library, the ftp client
has been modified to allow automatic determination
of a user's remote account. What this means is that you don't
need to know your remote account name on the target system, the
daemon, using your Distinguished Name (DN), will determine it
automatically from the gridmap file.

This is accomplished by having the client send over the string
":globus-mapping:" instead of a username. The daemon looks for this
string, and if detected gets the user's local name from the
gridmap file.

